\begin_layout Subsection
Joule or calorie?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In this work, a lot of work is done with energy.
 The SI unit of joules (J) is taken for this purpose.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There are different units for noting energy.
 In food, the calorie is the best known but also the most confusing.
 This is because a kilocalorie is actually used for food, but written down
 as a calorie.
 In joules, fortunately, this is not done.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
How can you convert one to the other? 1 (real) calorie equals 4.184
